title.narrative: Quality nutrition services for pregnant women, caregivers of girls and boys under 5 and adolescent girls strengthened

description.narrative: The life cycle approach that UNICEF is using as a strategy to deliver nutrition services has resulted in improving access to quality services to children, adolescents and women. As part of these, UNICEF supported FMOH deliver quality nutrition services in all health facilities (21,154) in the country. UNICEF with an aim to break intergenerational undernutrition, invested on improvement of adolescent nutrition and started to look at food transformation to improve diet of children. UNICEF also assisted GoE, to develop and implement program adjustment to implement lifesaving nutrition interventions during COVID-19 pandemic, ensuring continuation of essential services. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:24/08/2020
